### Outlet 1 — Hacker News (Show HN)
- Pitch route: public post, no editor gating. Write a Show HN thread with a working demo link.
- Exclusive norm: none (public post).
- Response window: engagement visible within 24 hours or it does not materialize.
- Prior contact: none. Current canonical first-target per BP075 fire order.
- Notes: Gate is v0.1.27 working + lianabanyan.com live + /proofs clean + $5/yr Stripe live (Wave 0 gate per BP075).

### Outlet 2 — Substack (own channel, launch)
- Pitch route: own channel, no editor. Direct publish.
- Exclusive norm: not applicable (own channel).
- Response window: immediate.
- Prior contact: "A Considered Approach" piece drafted (BP072), staged, not yet published.
- Notes: Substack is both a target and the fallback floor for pieces that primary outlets pass. Substack account setup is listed as an open Founder decision in BP069 close-stamp.

### Outlet 3 — Wired
- Pitch route: wired.com/about/contributor-guidelines — email pitch to assignments editor with a 200-word hook + draft link. Do not cold-send full piece.
- Exclusive norm: expects exclusive pitch during evaluation window (typically 2 weeks).
- Response window: 2 weeks typical; 4 weeks before silence-counts-as-rejection.
- Prior contact: none on file.
- Notes: Technology angle is the fit. "Free local AI vs paid flagships" or "Cooperative AI architecture" are both strong Wired frames. Anchor to Tier 3 benchmark receipt when it exists.

### Outlet 4 — The Atlantic
- Pitch route: theatlantic.com/contact/ — email pitch to Ideas section. 300-word pitch, no unsolicited full manuscripts.
- Exclusive norm: expects exclusive consideration, minimum 3 weeks.
- Response window: 3-4 weeks; 6 weeks before silence-counts-as-rejection.
- Prior contact: none on file.
- Notes: Long-form argument is the fit. "Memory-Wall Cure" or "Cooperative AI thesis" frames work here. Atlantic readers want the philosophical argument, not the benchmark chart.

### Outlet 5 — ProPublica
- Pitch route: propublica.org/getinvolved — pitch form. Best fit for investigative or accountability angle.
- Exclusive norm: expects exclusive during evaluation.
- Response window: 4-6 weeks.
- Prior contact: none on file.
- Notes: "Truth-Always discipline and verify-net" angle has a ProPublica fit if framed as accountability journalism about AI benchmarking fraud and how cooperative AI resists it.

### Outlet 6 — The Verge
- Pitch route: theverge.com — editorial contact via tips@theverge.com or direct editor LinkedIn. Short pitch (150 words), demo link required.
- Exclusive norm: flexible, often publishes concurrent coverage but prefers head-start.
- Response window: 1-2 weeks.
- Prior contact: none on file.
- Notes: The Verge wants the product story. "Free Gemma 4 12B vs paid flagships" with a working install link is the correct frame. Tier 3 benchmark receipt is the gate.

### Outlet 7 — NYT (re-engagement slot)
- Pitch route: nytimes.com/opinion — existing editorial contact from BP075/BP077 submission.
- Exclusive norm: standard exclusive submission. Do not re-submit the same piece that was already passed.
- Response window: 2-4 weeks.
- Prior contact: SENT (op-ed). Response: "passed until it proves in the wild." Re-engage only after proof-in-the-wild is demonstrable (HN traction + Substack readership + external benchmark replication + organic mesh nodes N >= 3).
- Notes: NYT re-engagement is a late-cadence slot, not an early target. Do not move it earlier.

### Outlet 8 — Cephas (always-on fallback)
- Pitch route: direct publish to lianabanyan.com. No editor gating.
- Exclusive norm: not applicable.
- Response window: immediate.
- Prior contact: Cephas is the home base, not an outreach target.
- Notes: Every ratified piece publishes here eventually. This is the proof-in-the-wild record.

### Backup Outlets (2-3 in reserve)

